---
import ElevationLayout from '../../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/elevation/Section.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';
import { productJsonLd } from '../../lib/structured-data';

const product = getProductBySlug('trust-architecture-complete')!;
const jsonLd = productJsonLd(product, 'https://evoked.dev/products/trust-architecture-complete');
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="Trust Architecture Complete"
  description="The complete trust practice: identity, voice, governance, and restraint. All four products, one price, the right build order. $149."
  structuredData={jsonLd}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["Products", "Full practice"]}
    headline="The complete trust practice."
    metaphor={["Identity. Voice. Governance. Restraint."]}
    sub="In the order they should be built."
  />

  <Section marker="FIG · I" heading="Why a bundle">
    <p class="lede">
      Trust isn't one thing. It's four architectural decisions working together.
      Identity without governance drifts. Governance without voice alienates.
      Voice without restraint manipulates. Restraint without identity has nothing
      to protect.
    </p>
    <p class="pd-body">
      The complete bundle gives you all four products in the order they should be
      built - so each layer strengthens the one before it.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · II" heading="What's included">
    <div class="pd-features">
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Trust Architecture Blueprint</h3>
        <p>The four-pillar framework. Persona file templates, session protocols, graduated trust stages, and quarterly reviews. Start here.</p>
        <a href="/products/trust-architecture-blueprint" class="pd-feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Agent Voice Architecture Guide</h3>
        <p>Three-level voice framework - protection, respect, nurturance. Sovereignty language audit, voice specifications, and refusal voice patterns.</p>
        <a href="/products/agent-voice-architecture-guide" class="pd-feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Agent Governance Starter Kit</h3>
        <p>Charter template, boundary specifications, drift monitoring thresholds, and four-level accountability framework.</p>
        <a href="/products/agent-governance-starter-kit" class="pd-feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Agent Restraint Specification</h3>
        <p>Boundary audit, refusal category matrix, fail-mode decisions, accountability architecture, and adversarial testing checklist.</p>
        <a href="/products/agent-restraint-specification" class="pd-feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · III" heading="The build order">
    <div class="pd-pillars">
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">1</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Blueprint first</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Understand the four pillars. Define your agent's identity. Everything else builds on this."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">2</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Voice second</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Design how your agent speaks - and what it will never say. Voice is where identity meets the user."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">3</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Governance third</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Set the boundaries, thresholds, and accountability chains. Structure that holds when you're not watching."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">4</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Restraint last</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Specify what the agent must refuse. Restraint is the final layer - it protects everything you've built."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · IV" heading="Who this is for">
    <div class="pd-audience">
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Teams going all-in</h3>
        <p>You've decided trust architecture matters. The bundle gives you the complete practice without piecemealing it together over months.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Agencies and consultancies</h3>
        <p>Building agent systems for clients. The four-product framework gives you a repeatable trust architecture process you can apply across engagements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Organizations scaling agents</h3>
        <p>Moving from one agent to many. The trust architecture that worked for a single agent needs structural reinforcement at scale. This is it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · V" heading="Buy the complete bundle">
    <div class="pd-purchase">
      <div class="pd-price">$149</div>
      <p class="pd-savings">Save $47 vs. buying individually ($196)</p>
      <p class="pd-purchase-lead">Four PDFs. The complete trust architecture practice.</p>
      <a
        href={product.stripePaymentLink}
        class="pd-buy-cta"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >Buy the Complete Bundle</a>
      <p class="pd-purchase-fineprint">
        Includes Trust Architecture Blueprint, Agent Voice Architecture Guide,
        Agent Governance Starter Kit, and Agent Restraint Specification Template.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="NOTA · BENE" heading="Go deeper" closing={true}>
    <p class="lede">
      The bundle gives you the frameworks. If you want hands-on help implementing
      them, three doorways from here.
    </p>
    <div class="pd-upsell">
      <a href="/case-studies/labyrinth" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>See it in practice</h3>
        <p>We analyzed a real defensive AI security platform through the four pillars. See what trust architecture looks like in the wild.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Read the case study &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/consulting" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>Trust Architecture Workshop</h3>
        <p>Full-day guided implementation on your agent system with your team. I facilitate. You see. $8,000.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Learn more &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="pd-upsell-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <h3>Discovery call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your trust architecture and figure out next steps.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Schedule &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>

<style>
  /* Product detail template - reused from trust-architecture-blueprint.
     Two additions on this page (and reusable on others):
       .pd-feature-link  - inline "Learn more" link inside a pd-feature
       .pd-savings       - the savings line in the purchase card */

  .pd-body {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.1rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  /* ---- FIG II: feature grid ---- */
  .pd-features {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 1vw, 1.5rem);
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .pd-feature {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .pd-feature:hover { border-color: var(--el-accent); }
  .pd-feature h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .pd-feature p {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 0.9rem + 0.2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .pd-feature-link {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    align-self: flex-start;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
  .pd-feature-link:hover { color: var(--el-text); }

  /* ---- FIG III: pillar list (numbered) ---- */
  .pd-pillars {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-pillar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 1vw, 1.75rem);
    padding: clamp(1rem, 0.85rem + 0.6vw, 1.5rem) clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-pillar:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .pd-pillar-number {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 1.25rem + 1.5vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    line-height: 0.9;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .pd-pillar-body { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
  .pd-pillar-body h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
  }
  .pd-pillar-question {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 0.85rem + 0.2vw, 1rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .pd-pillar { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .pd-pillar-number { width: auto; text-align: left; }
  }

  /* ---- FIG IV: audience cards ---- */
  .pd-audience {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 1vw, 1.5rem);
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .pd-audience-card {
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-audience-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .pd-audience-card p {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 0.9rem + 0.2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- FIG V: purchase card ---- */
  .pd-purchase {
    max-width: 520px;
    margin: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem) auto 0;
    padding: clamp(1.75rem, 1.25rem + 1.5vw, 2.75rem);
    border: 2px solid var(--el-accent);
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--el-accent) 6%, transparent);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .pd-price {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 1.75rem + 2.5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .pd-savings {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .pd-purchase-lead {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 0.9rem + 0.25vw, 1.1rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .pd-buy-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
    background: var(--el-accent);
    color: var(--el-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-accent);
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .pd-buy-cta:hover {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--el-accent);
  }
  .pd-purchase-fineprint {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.8rem, 0.75rem + 0.2vw, 0.9rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  /* ---- NOTA BENE: upsell cards ---- */
  .pd-upsell {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);
    margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .pd-upsell-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 1.75rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .pd-upsell-card:hover { border-color: var(--el-accent); }
  .pd-upsell-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--el-display);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.3vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-text);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .pd-upsell-card p {
    font-family: var(--el-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 0.85rem + 0.2vw, 1rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--el-text-soft);
    margin: 0;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .pd-upsell-link {
    font-family: var(--el-ui);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--el-accent);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
